      <h3>How Many Hours Can You Expect?</h3>
      <p>Part-time roles typically offer 15–30 hours per week. Retail and food service schedules are often irregular — you may work 20 hours one week and 12 the next. Warehouse and delivery roles tend to offer more consistent hours. Remote customer service often has fixed part-time shifts (e.g., 25 hours/week).</p>
      <p>At 20 hours per week at $15/hour, monthly pre-tax income is approximately $1,200 — or roughly $14,400 per year. At 30 hours per week at $20/hour, that rises to about $2,600/month ($31,200/year). These are realistic ranges for someone working part-time without experience.</p>
